                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/599a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Brown Bros. &amp; Co. and Seligman &amp; Co</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: Please find enclosed carbon copy of a
                        letter<note n="1" xml:id="d1353fn1">See next above.</note> addressed to
                    Pedro Rafael Cuadra, Minister of Finance of Nicaragua.</p>
                <p>I understood in my telephonic conversation with Mr. Thatcher Brown that there
                    would be no objection to incorporating this clause in the proper contract.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
